-- Portugal’s Trade Gap Narrows as Exports Increase, Imports Drop
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2012-05-10T10:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-10/portugal-s-trade-gap-narrows-as-exports-increase-imports-drop.html
Portugal ’s  trade deficit  narrowed in
the first quarter as exports rose and imports decreased, the
country’s statistics institute said.  The trade deficit narrowed to 2.68 billion euros ($3.5
billion) from 4.35 billion euros in the first three months of
2011, the Lisbon-based institute said today in an e-mailed
report. Exports rose 11.6 percent and imports fell 3.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joao Lima in Lisbon at 
